Poland:
Death of Władysław II Jagiełło
Coronation of Władysław III of Varna
Russia:
Vasily II burned Galich.
The army of Yury Dmitrievich defeated the army of Vasily II. The latter fled to Nizhny Novgorod.
Dmitrievich arrived in Moscow and again declared himself the Grand Prince.
Dmitrievich died. His oldest son Vasili Kosoy, the Cross-Eyed, succeeded him as Grand Prince.
Sweden: Start of Engelbrekt rebellion against King Erik of Pomerania
